  "page": 181,
  "spans": [
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0002",
      "text": " 162",
      "bbox": [
        518.28,
        723.59,
        537.71,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0003",
      "text": "6.6.5.4.3  Stacked Connect-requests",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        266.46,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0004",
      "text": "The Stack Connect-request bits (word 0, bits 29 - 28) are used in the Fabric Login procedure.  They",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        82.97,
        540.07,
        94.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0005",
      "text": "are only meaningful for Class 1 in the FLOGI LS_ACC.  They are not meaningful for other classes",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        94.97,
        540.02,
        106.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0006",
      "text": "and other Class 1 login frames.  Table 160 specifies the meaning of the combination of word 0 bits 29",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        106.97,
        540.04,
        118.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0007",
      "text": "and 28.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        118.97,
        129.3,
        130.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0008",
      "text": "Support for stacked connect-requests is optional in both a Fabric and Nx_Port.  Both an Nx_Port's",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        262.97,
        540.0,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0009",
      "text": "and Fx_Port's behavior change if stacked connect-requests are functional (see FC-FS-2).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        274.96,
        490.67,
        286.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0010",
      "text": "6.6.5.4.4  Sequential delivery",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        298.96,
        231.57,
        310.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0011",
      "text": "0 = Out of order delivery allowed",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        322.96,
        240.02,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0012",
      "text": "1 = Sequential delivery requested",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        334.96,
        244.6,
        346.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0013",
      "text": "The Sequential delivery bit (word 0, bit 27) is only meaningful for the class 2 and 3 N_Port Class Ser-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        358.96,
        540.08,
        370.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0014",
      "text": "vice Parameters in Fabric Login.  Out of order frame delivery in class 2 and 3 is the default function",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        370.96,
        540.0,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0015",
      "text": "by a Fabric.  It is not meaningful for Class 1, or Class 6 or for N_Port Login.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        382.96,
        428.7,
        394.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0016",
      "text": "If this bit is set to one by an Nx_Port, it is requesting that all frames delivered to the Nx_Port request-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        406.96,
        540.07,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0017",
      "text": "ing this function be delivered in the same order in which the frames were transmitted by the source",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        418.96,
        539.87,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0018",
      "text": "Nx_Port.  If this bit is set to one by the Fx_Port in the LS_ACC, the Fx_Port shall deliver Class 2 and",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        430.96,
        539.92,
        442.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0019",
      "text": "3 frames in the same order as transmitted from any one Nx_Port in the absence of Fabric events",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        442.96,
        540.0,
        454.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0020",
      "text": "(e.g., Fabric reconfiguration or zoning changes).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        454.96,
        308.75,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0021",
      "text": "A Fabric supporting the sequential delivery feature routes Class 2 and 3 frames via a fixed route",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        478.96,
        539.92,
        490.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0022",
      "text": "through the Fabric to provide in-order frame delivery.  This feature does not imply any other alteration",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        490.96,
        539.92,
        502.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0023",
      "text": "to the normal class of service functions (e.g., F_BSY responses are still possible in Class 2 and",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        502.96,
        539.99,
        514.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0024",
      "text": "Class 3 frames may still be discarded by the Fabric based on normal Class 2 and 3 rules).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        514.96,
        493.62,
        526.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0025",
      "text": "If this bit is set to one, the Fabric attempts to maintain the order of delivery of both Data and",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        538.96,
        539.96,
        550.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0026",
      "text": "Link_Control (Class 2 only) frames to the Nx_Port requesting this feature in the same order in which",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        550.96,
        540.04,
        562.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0027",
      "text": "the frames were transmitted.  Table 161 specifies the meaning of the combination of the Sequential",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        562.96,
        540.04,
        574.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0028",
      "text": "delivery bit for the requesting Nx_Port and the applicable Fx_Port.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        574.96,
        387.59,
        586.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0029",
      "text": " Table 160 – Stacked Connect-request support Login Bits",
      "bbox": [
        182.22,
        140.98,
        453.81,
        152.1
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0030",
      "text": "Word 0, bits 29 - 28",
      "bbox": [
        128.46,
        163.0,
        219.49,
        174.11
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0031",
      "text": "Meaning",
      "bbox": [
        369.71,
        163.0,
        410.24,
        174.11
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0032",
      "text": "00b",
      "bbox": [
        103.98,
        179.98,
        120.61,
        191.09
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p181_s0033",
